    "kit": {
      "info": {
        "contact": {
          "name": "Sodeom Support",
          "url": "https://sodeom.com"
        },
        "description": "This API serves as a proxy to an OpenAI-compatible API utilizing GitHub Models. It allows users to send queries or chat history and receive generated text responses, ensuring privacy and no tracking.",
        "license": {
          "name": "Proprietary"
        },
        "servers": [
          {
            "description": "Production server",
            "url": "https://sodeom.com"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Sodeom AI Proxy",
        "version": "1.0.0",
        "tagline": "OpenAI-compatible proxy that forwards chat completions to GitHub Models, with no API key required from callers",
        "homepage": "https://sodeom.com",
        "docs_url": "https://sodeom.com/apis/ai",
        "license_short": "Proprietary; free public proxy operated by Sodeom (Abdul Hadi).",
        "license_md": "- Proprietary service provided by Sodeom (built by Abdul Hadi).\n- Free to use as a public proxy; no API key is required (\"pass anything\").\n- GitHub token authentication to the upstream GitHub Models API happens server-side.\n- No explicit rate limits or SLA are published; treat the service as best-effort.",
        "about_md": "Sodeom AI Proxy is a small public HTTP service operated by [Sodeom](https://sodeom.com) (Abdul Hadi) that exposes an OpenAI-compatible interface in front of [GitHub Models](https://github.com/marketplace/models). It lets you call familiar chat-completion endpoints without managing your own GitHub token, so any OpenAI SDK can be pointed at it by changing only the base URL.\n\nWhat you get from the API:\n\n- A simple `GET /ai?query=...` endpoint that returns `{\"answer\": \"...\"}` for one-shot questions.\n- An OpenAI-shaped `POST /v1/chat/completions` endpoint accepting `messages`, `model`, `temperature`, `max_tokens`, `top_p`, `stop`, `frequency_penalty`, `presence_penalty`, `seed`, `n`, and `stream`.\n- A `GET /v1/models` endpoint listing the supported models (including `gpt-4o-mini` as the default, `gpt-4o`, `o1-mini`, and Meta Llama variants).\n- Server-Sent-Events streaming on chat completions.\n\nOperational notes: CORS is enabled, no caller-side API key is required (the proxy supplies its own GitHub token upstream), and there is no published rate limit. Health monitoring on the community catalogue page reports an average response time around 2.5 seconds and roughly 80% reliability, so the service is suitable for experimentation and demos rather than production workloads.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "ain": "The AI proxy resource — wraps the OpenAI-compatible chat surface exposed at `/ai` and `/v1/chat/completions`, forwarded to GitHub Models.",
          "ain2": "A secondary grouping for the same AI proxy surface, covering the model-listing endpoint at `/v1/models` alongside the chat-completion operations."
        },
        "auth": false
      },
